SIMPLE: fragility
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fragility
<hw>Fra*gil"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fragilitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>fragilit⟦eacute⟧</ets>. Cf.
<er>Frailty</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition or quality of
being fragile; brittleness; frangibility.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Weakness; feebleness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An appearance of delicacy, and even of <qex>fragility</qex>, is
almost essential to it [beauty].</q> <rj><qau>Burke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Liability to error and sin; frailty.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>fragility</qex> and youthful folly of Qu. Fabius.</q>
<rj><qau>Holland.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fragment</ent>⟦br⟧
